ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY

Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How logical does the treatment you are receiving seem to you?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = Maybe logical; 3 = A little logical; 4 = Somewhat logical; 5 = Fairly logical; 6 = Mostly logical; 7 = Very logical

ElementDescription: How confident are you that this treatment will be successful in eliminating your insomnia?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = Maybe confident; 3 = A little confident; 4 = Somewhat confident; 5 = Fairly confident; 6 = Mostly confident; 7 = Very confident

ElementDescription: How confident would you be in recommending this treatment to a friend?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = Maybe confident; 3 = A little confident; 4 = Somewhat confident; 5 = Fairly confident; 6 = Mostly confident; 7 = Very confident

ElementDescription: How willing are you (were you) to undergo this treatment?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = Maybe willing; 3 = A little willing; 4 = Somewhat willing; 5 = Fairly willing; 6 = Mostly willing; 7 = Very willing

ElementDescription: How successful do you think this treatment is for treating other people with insomnia?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = Maybe successful; 3 = A little successful; 4 = Somewhat successful; 5 = Fairly successful; 6 = Mostly successful; 7 = Very successful
